sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: REX_Coding
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The REX is linked with signal peptide of Zim17, GAL promoter and ADH1 terminator. When expressed in cytoplasm, it will be located into mitochondrial matrix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiaopeng Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: All parts should be correctly linked without frame shift.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SP_REX
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: REX is tagged with signal peptide of ZIM17, thus can be targetted into mitochondrial matrix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiaopeng Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part BBa_K809201 and BBa_K809401 should be correctly linked without frame shift

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SPzim17
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: this part is the sequence of transit signal peptide of ZIM17. It can help protein target to the mitochondrial matrix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Zim17, a novel zinc finger protein essential for protein import into mitochondria. J Biol Chem. 2004 Nov 26 ;279(48):50243-9. Epub 2004 Sep 21 . http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P42844
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: it is synthesized based on the complete sequence of signal peptide of ZIM17

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: REX
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This biobrick is the coding sequence of our SU9+REX in yeast cytoplasm. It is used to construct our final biobricks which express REX in the cytoplasm and then transport REX into mitochondrial matrix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiaopeng Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: SU9 comes from yeast gemome. REX was modified to suitable for expression in yeast.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The signal peptid must be able to work efficiently, and can transport REX into mitochondrial matrix.
